Samsung has announced that the Galaxy S9 and S9+ will now be available to US consumers in 128GB and 256GB storage options. “The new phones will offer Galaxy users the freedom to capture more images, download more apps, and enjoy more content than previously possible on the Galaxy S9 and S9+,” said the company. In South Africa, many retailers only stock the 64GB model of the Galaxy S9, and the 128GB model of the Galaxy S9+. The devices also support a microSD card up to 400GB in size.